1. Opening Tag

The starting tag of an element.

Example:

<p>
2. Closing Tag

The ending tag with /.

Example:

</p>

3. Self-Closing Tag

A tag that closes itself.

Example:

<br />
<hr />
<img src="image.jpg" />

4. Empty Tag

A tag with no content inside it.

Examples:

<br>
<hr>
<input>

These are also called void elements in HTML.